Package: treesitter.r
Title: R Grammar for tree-sitter
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Davis", "Vaughan", , "davis@posit.co", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Posit Software, PBC", role = c("cph", "fnd"))
  )
Description: Provides bindings to an R grammar for tree-sitter, to be used
    alongside the 'treesitter' package. Tree-sitter builds concrete syntax
    trees for source files of any language, and can efficiently update
    those syntax trees as the source file is edited.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Depends:
    R (>= 4.0.0)
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    treesitter
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Config/build/bootstrap: TRUE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
Remotes:
    treesitter=DavisVaughan/r-tree-sitter
